arts.ttl: Northampton and Stevenage start the new year with goalless draw
Stevenage held to a dull 0-0 draw at Northampton Town
arts.sum: Instead you get to point the finger at a lack of forward impetus by Stevenage as they failed to create any meaningful attack until the fourth minute of stoppage time at the end of the first half. Tarqie Fosu had another effort for Northampton, curled wide of the far post, and it was at that point Boro responded with their first sub, Harvey White coming on for Dan Kemp.
